# No Tab Autocomplete in Problem Solutions

When working on files in the `problems/` directory:

- Do NOT use tab completion to write solution logic
- Do NOT suggest or auto-complete algorithmic code
- Do NOT provide the solution, even partially
- You may autocomplete:
  - Import statements
  - Type definitions and interfaces
  - Test harness / boilerplate code
  - Console.log statements for debugging
  - Helper class definitions (ListNode, TreeNode, etc.)

The purpose of this repo is to practice problem-solving. Autocompleting solutions defeats the purpose.
